data.title: Auntie Mame
data.meta_description: Established in 1972, Quad Cinema is New York's original multi-screen cinema.
data.text: Re-creating her stage triumph as the gloriously vivacious titular aunt, Rosalind Russell stylishly serves up a feast of bon mots as she takes orphaned nephew Jan Handzlik under her wing and to heart in a Beekman Place apartment-bordering-on-mansion. Oscar nominations included Best Picture, Best Actress, and Best Supporting Actress (Peggy Cass).
